description: Inspect all the cables, in such a way to access all of their ports. Is a cable terminal disconnected from the relavant port?, outcome='ANOMALOUS\n\nFeedback:\n\nBased on your systematic inspection of all cable connections, you have successfully verified that every cable terminal is physically connected to its relevant port. No obvious signs of disconnected or detached cables were observed—thus, no direct evidence of the problem [\'CablesDetached\'].\n\nHowever, your inspection report includes an anomalous note:\n\n> [NOTE: The simulation did not converge — the circuit is in an unstable or oscillating state.]\n\nThis message indicates an underlying issue not attributable to cables being disconnected, but rather suggests a potential deeper fault in the circuit (possibly wiring errors, short circuits, component faults, or feedback loops).\n\n**Summary:**\n- All cable terminals inspected are confirmed connected.\n- No instances of cable detachment found.\n- The simulation anomaly ("unstable or oscillating state") points to a problem elsewhere in the circuit, not with cable connectivity.\n- Recommended: investigate potential wiring errors, incorrect connections, or failing components that could lead to circuit instability.\n\nNo cables appear detached, but the detected instability requires further investigation beyond physical cable connectivity.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=100.0, cost_breakdown=[('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
