description: Make sure the lamp is properly installed in its holder, outcome='ANOMALOUS\n\nFeedback:\nThe lamp ("Main Load (lamp)") is observed to be lit and has no observable internal fault. However, the note regarding "simulation did not converge — the circuit is in an unstable or oscillating state" is an anomalous observation. This suggests possible improper installation or other issues affecting circuit stability. Further investigation into the installation and circuit connections is recommended to rule out the problem \'LampImproperlyInstalled\'.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=10.0, cost_breakdown=[('observe_component', 10.0)], simplified_outcome=None)] 
